Not really. Perhaps the best you could do is reset the SNES, then run a custom program that dumps the SPC-700 RAM. The main problem is that you don't know the CPU register state prior to reset. This approach would have the same problem on any system, really.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Wed Oct 15, 2008 4:32 pm</p><hr />
